  "body": "https://github.com/Consensys/teku/pull/7698 changed Teku's default behaviour when syncing.\n\nWe need to make a few improvements in the logs to help users:\n- When printing the error because the initial state is too old (out of weak subjectivity period), add a reference to the flag option to bypass this check (`--ignore-weak-subjectivity-period-enabled`).\n- Include a link to the docs page in the error message.\n- When the user is using the `--ignore-weak-subjectivity-period-enabled`, we should still print a log message about it just to be clear that this isn't the safest option and they should know what they are doing.\n- \nRelated to #7698",
